{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7b36b6500d13a3ede", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70f9a489afa3080ade2d"], "chapters": ["615d6ff12b295b085ab6ec06"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "37", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "In flowering plants, double fertilization and triple fusion is a unique phenomenon. For a given plant, during the study of the endosperm, it was found that it has 24 chromosomes. What will the number of chromosomes in microspore mother cells?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "v94CO", "text": "12", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "ZPJ2g", "text": "48", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "o8sN1", "text": "16", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "QuL4e", "text": "24", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "The endosperm is triploid in nature in angiosperms, while microspore mother cells are diploid structures.<br /><br />Since the number of chromosomes in the endosperm is 24 = 3n. Therefore n = 8.<br /><br />Hence, the number of chromosomes in the microspore mother cell will be 2n = 2x8 =16.<br />&nbsp;", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["616057290283de43c87e3e1a", "616057b00283de43c87e3e20", "64d50cd33df7f4a7f3017f71", "66b79bbbd4b564dfab4f94d2", "67fa60d64468eb1307ceb0b0", "6807d392647479b8e869647c"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616025c322cc696a9491eb44", "616025c2822b7bb5e27982e5", "64eb06ed3118f713ecfef24a", "66d5854ca75f05ee8564f626", "67fdff51378e1624ea7b6